The paper discusses the development of a new lightweight digital signature scheme suitable for resource-constrained embedded devices, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the emerging ubiquitous systems and the Internet of Things (IoT), which are relevant to the categories of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper involves cryptographic tools and optimization techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
